<subSubSection pageId="75" pageNumber="559" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="75.[739,1331,3038,3462]" pageId="75" pageNumber="559">
<taxonomicName box="[743,994,3153,3186]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Vampyressa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="559" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thyone">Vampyressa thyone</taxonomicName>
was associated with V. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="P. Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[777,869,3192,3225]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Micronycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="559" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minuta">minuta</taxonomicName>
by G. S. Miller, Jr. in 1912 (from 
<collectingCountry box="[740,853,3232,3265]" name="Panama" pageId="75" pageNumber="559">Panama</collectingCountry>
) and V. venilla by O. Thomas in 1924 (from northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1068,1139,3275,3304]" name="Peru" pageId="75" pageNumber="559">Peru</collectingCountry>
); however, it more commonly has been treated as a synonym or subspecies of V. 
<taxonomicName box="[1093,1182,3350,3383]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Vampyressa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="559" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusilla">pusilla</taxonomicName>
. B. K. Lim and collaborators in 2003 confirmed that it is a distinct species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
